metadata.name: SUBMERG
metadata.description:
In the depths of despair,  
A human being does dwell,  
Lost in the darkness,  
Of their own private hell.

The weight of the world,  
Rests heavy on their soul,  
As they struggle to cope,  
With a life out of control.

Their thoughts spiral downward,  
Into a bottomless pit,  
As they drown in sadness,  
And can't seem to quit.

But amidst the shadows,  
There's a flicker of light,  
A glimmer of hope,  
That can make things right.

Though the road is long,  
And the journey is tough,  
They must keep pushing forward,  
For it's never enough.

There's beauty in the struggle,  
And strength in the pain,  
As they rise from the darkness,  
And find peace once again.

For the human spirit is resilient,  
And can overcome any test,  
So let hope be their guide,  
As they rise above the rest.
